articles.author: Parisa Hafezi, Emily Rose
articles.description: Israel hit back at Iran early on Saturday, with its military saying it was conducting strikes against military targets in response to Tehran's attacks on Israel.
articles.title: Israel hits back at Iran with strikes on military targets, IDF says

articles.author: Jonathan Landay
articles.description: One expert said the strikes may have hampered Iran's ability to mass-produce missiles.
articles.title: Exclusive: Satellite photos show Israel hit Iran missile fuel-mixing facilities, researchers say

articles.author: Sakura Murakami
articles.description: Political wrangling could roil markets and be a headache for the Bank of Japan.
articles.title: Japan votes in election expected to punish PM Ishiba's coalition

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Israeli forces withdrew from a hospital complex in northern Gaza on Saturday, one day after storming it, and the Palestinian enclave's health ministry said the troops had detained dozens of male medical staffers and some of the patients.
articles.title: Israeli army leaves north Gaza hospital, detains medics, says health ministry

articles.author: Felix Light, Lucy Papachristou
articles.description: Georgians vote on Saturday in a parliamentary election depicted by both sides as an existential battle that will determine whether the country integrates closely with the West or leans back towards Moscow.
articles.title: Georgia votes in election seen as stark choice between Russia and West

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A gang attack in Port-au-Prince forced residents to flee their homes on Saturday as the gangs operating in and around the Haitian capital ramp up attacks on areas they do not yet control.
articles.title: Residents in Haiti's capital flee homes as gangs expand control

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Washington Post reported on Saturday that South African-born billionaire businessman Elon Musk worked illegally in the United States during a brief period in the 1990s while building a startup company.
articles.title: Washington Post reports Elon Musk briefly worked illegally in US in 1990s

articles.author: Michael Holden
articles.description: Right-wing, anti-immigrant protesters and opposing anti-racism demonstrators are both planning large rallies in London on Saturday, closely watched by a beefed up police operation aimed at heading off any clashes between the rival gatherings.
articles.title: Police gear up for large, rival London protests

articles.author: Sergio Goncalves, Miguel Pereira
articles.description: Thousands of people took to the main avenue of downtown Lisbon on Saturday to protest police violence, several days after a policeman shot a Cape Verde-born Portuguese resident, triggering a wave of unrest.
articles.title: Thousands protest in Lisbon against police violence

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: At least 24 people died and five others were injured when a bus crashed on a highway in Mexico's central state of Zacatecas on Saturday, local authorities said.
articles.title: Two dozen people die in bus crash in central Mexico
